            of all the partitioned datasets on a volume.  Please note
            how IEHMAP attempts to format the directory entries of
            pds members as if they are load modules.  The main advantage
            of IEHMAP in this function is that it is very quick, taking
            a small fraction of a minute to list all the pds members
            on a large volume.

CL9608AU.text:
Figure 1   Sample Output from Walter Shelley's PTF Cross Reference
           Program.

           This program reads a PTF file as it comes from IBM on a
           CBPDO tape or other maintenance tape.  This program
           classifies the PTFs by which product they belong to.
           This is useful information for a collection of PTFs,
           which is not easily obtained using IBM-supplied methods.
           You can easily verify or second-guess IBM to make sure
           they sent you the right maintenance.
